This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for propaganda detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to NLP and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of neural models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments and ablation studies, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper analyzes the performance of the models on different propaganda techniques, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
